title: For Sale:  CZ82 with 2 mags, holster, and 250 + rounds of ammo - deal pending-
postcontent: This is a really nice mid sized pistol. It is in 9x18 which is slightly more powerful than a .380. The ammo is cheap and readily available (unlike .380!) It is super accurate, even with the steel cased ammo. I've shot over 200 rounds without a single malfunction. People like it b/c it can be carried "cocked and locked" or double action/single action. Trigger pull is superb. It has ambi safeties AND mag releases, which is nice as I shoot lefty, and you never know when you will be forced to use your weak side. Unlike a 1911, there is no grip safety. Some people don't want the grip safety, but if you are used to the 1911 that is one thing to keep in mind, especially when you unload it. The mags hold 12 rounds. I have 2. Unfortunately, mags are like $40 a piece! The gun is old school all steel construction so it is heavy for its size. I have fairly wide hands, my little finger doesn't quite fit on the gun. It fits my wife's hands perfectly. A great pistol for the price!

title: For Sale/Trade:  Colt Agent .38 Special 15oz, 6-shot +p rated
postcontent:
So, here is a rare one for you -- a Colt Agent .38 Special.

Basically this gun was the budget version of the Cobra D-Frame snubby revolver made in the early 80s -- making it one of the last of the old-school Colt revolvers with hand fitted internal lockwork -- in-fact, it has the same amazing Colt lockworks and guts as a Cobra, but with a cheaper parkerized finish. It also has an alloy frame for much reduced weight -- somepeople think that the alloy framed Agent is the best CC revolver Colt ever made. 

Basic Specs:
Marque -- Colt
Model -- Agent
Caliber -- .38 Special (factory rated for +p ammunition)
Weight -- 15oz
Capacity -- 6 rounds

This gun shows minor holster wear, with low round count.  Very smooth DA and SA trigger, locks up "bank vault" tight, just like a Colt should. The timing is dead on, and it shoots just like it should. 

Comes with original triangular walnut stocks w/ bronze medallions (in excellent condition), a set of modified Detective Special stocks, and a set of Hogue Monogrips (currently mounted).  A couple speed loaders are also available for the right deal.

I'm only selling because I tricked out my S&W 442 with a fancy trigger job and CT laser grips, and just don't cary it enough anymore to justify keeping it.

Asking $500, OBRO.  FTF in Portland.  OR DL required, CHL preferred.

An intuitive, thumb-operated safety can be accessed without compromising the firing grip and allows the shooter to maintain a solid weld to the adjustable cheek piece. title: For Sale:  Colt 1911 Series 70 / 1991 .38 Super Semi Auto Pistol In A Box
location: Hudson Valley, Hudson Valley, New York
postcontent:
Make: Colt 

Model: 1911 Government Model, Series '70 .38 Super slide, mated to a Series 1991 frame. 

Serial Number: 2753408 

Year of Manufacture: Modern 

Caliber: .38 Super. 

Action Type: Semi-Auto Pistol 

Markings: The left side of the slide is marked, "Colt's Mark IV / Series '70 / Government Model / .38 Super Auto Caliber" followed by the Rampant Colt logo. The right side of the slide is marked "Colt's Government Model." The right side of the frame is marked, "Colt's Pt. F A Mfg. Co, Hartford, Conn. U.S.A.". The serial number "2753408" is stamped on the right side of the frame. The barrel is marked “Colt Super 38 Auto / MK IV Series 70 “. 

Barrel Length: 5 inches 

Sights / Optics: The gun is mounted with a very interesting and useful sight package; what appears to be a Smith and Wesson windage-and-elevation adjustable rear sight, with a unique, broad, serrated, semi-Partridge, semi-ramp front sight. 

Stock Configuration & Condition: The grips are Colt hard rubber, checkered grips, with the Colt Rampant horse logo on each panel. The grips rate in about Excellent overall condition. 

Type of Finish: Gloss blue finish on the slide, with the matte-blue Series '91 finish on the frame. 

Finish Originality: The frame appears original while the slide looks reblued. 

Bore Condition: The bore is clean and bright and the rifling is sharp. There is evidence of use, but not abuse. 

Overall Condition: This gun retains about 90% of its metal finish. There is evidence of use, perhaps holster wear, although this is extremely minor. There is general light edge wear and some uneven finishing on the slide. The Screw heads are sharp, though previously turned. The markings are clear though slightly lightened on the slide. Overall, this gun rates in about Very Good condition. 

Mechanics: The action functions correctly though not smoothly. The slide drops when held back and released, but when eased forward hangs up a bit. the slide stop does not hold open on an empty magazine, with either magazine. 

Box, Paperwork & Accessories: This pistol comes with TWO .38 Super magazines, delivered in a correct Series '91 Colt blue plastic lockable box, with case candy; the orange warning tag, an unused warranty card, congratulatory letter, "the Colt Companion" pamphlet, a list of warranty repair stations, and an environmental warning (!) all in a plastic baggie.

title: For Sale:  SMITH & WESSON PRE-MODEL 10 -- .38 M&P...SCARCE 5 ROUND-BUTT...Mfd 1949,
postcontent: Here's an unusual variation of the classic Smith & Wesson ".38 Military & Police" revolver. Chambered for the .38 Special, this revolver is built on the Round-Butt K-frame with five screws. It wears a 5-inch barrel with fixed service sights. Condition is excellent and all serial numbered parts are properly matching, including the original diamond checkered stocks. The original blue finish rates about 98% with a cylinder turn line and a tiny bit of handling wear. There are no scratches or dings; no rust or pitting. The stocks are in excellent condition as well, free of cracks, chips or gouges. Vivid case colors remain on hammer and trigger. The mechanics are in perfect working order with good timing and solid lock-up. The bore is likewise excellent with bright/sharp rifling. This fine revolver appears little more than test fired! It comes in the original 2-piece gold & blue picture box that is numbered to the gun. The revolver specifications on the end of the box were factory modified by overstamping the "Square" (Butt) and adding "Round". A round butt, long barreled post-war K-frame is a scarce bird..
